HEADWORD: Dorhawk
<hw>Dor"hawk`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The European goatsucker; -- so called because it eats the
<xex>dor</xex> beetle. See <er>Goatsucker</er>.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>dorrhawk</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Booth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

